    <stitle>ALLISON WT TRANSMISSION ELECTRONIC CONTROLS - WT TRANSMISSION DIAGNOSTIC CODES</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>WT TRANSMISSION DIAGNOSTIC CODES</title>
        <svcsubsecinfo>
            <para>Illumination of the DO NOT SHIFT or SERVICE light during vehicle operation (start-up) indicates that
                the ECU has registered a diagnostic code.
            </para>
        </svcsubsecinfo>
        <svcproc svcproctype="diagnose" graphiccount="0">
            <title>DIAGNOSTIC CODE MEMORY</title>
            <para>This service manual section provides a "limited" discussion of the Allison WT diagnostic fault codes.
                For a complete, in-depth discussion, refer to the Allison WT Transmission Service Manual.
            </para>
            <para>Diagnostic codes are logged in a list in ECU memory (EEPROM). Up to five codes can be registered in
                the ECU at one time with the most recent code appearing first on the list. The code list contains the
                information listed in the following chart:
