            <para>*"MODE ON" INDICATOR</para>
            <para>ON = ACTIVE</para>
            <para>OFF = INACTIVE</para>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>ALL INFORMATION IN CHART IS AVAILABLE WITH PRO-LINK DDR.</para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <para>The following defines the different parts of the list contained in ECU memory:</para>
            <seqlist style="arabic">
                <item>
                    <para>Code List Position - Identifies where the code ranks in list: first, second, third, etc. up to
                        position five. Position one indicates which code occurred most recently.
                    </para>
                    <para>If a new diagnostic incident occurs and needs to be logged and the list already contains five
                        codes, the oldest "inactive" code will be dropped when the newest code takes the number 1
                        position. If all codes on the list are active, then the oldest "active" code is dropped, unless
                        the code is on the "severity" code list.
                    </para>
                    <para>The Severity List (located in the Allison WT Service Manual) contains diagnostic incident
                        codes that must be written to the EEPROM immediately so that they are "remembered" if an ECU
                        abnormal power-down occurs. The Severity List includes all output speed sensor failure codes (to
                        prevent possible downshifts after re-initialization) and all solenoid A and Solenoid B failed
                        hydraulically ON codes (to prevent re-initialization in neutral with C1 clutch or C2 clutch
                        applied).
                    </para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Main Code - Identifies the general condition or fault detected by the ECU.</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Sub Code - Identifies a more specific area or condition under the main code in which the
                        condition was detected.
                    </para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Active Indicator - Is set to ON when the diagnostic incident occurs and will indicate OFF if
                        on the next ignition cycle no "inhibits" resulted from the incident causing the code to
                        register. An active code means that the condition that caused the diagnostic code to register is
                        present in the system.
                    </para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Ignition Cycle Counter - Is used to clear codes that are inactive from the code list in
                        memory. After 25 ignition cycles (vehicle started) any code will be deleted from the list if the
                        diagnostic incident that caused the code has not happened again. The Ignition Cycle Counter can
                        only be viewed using a diagnostic data reader.
                    </para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Event Counter - Logs the number of times that the diagnostic event occurs, causing the code to
                        be written to memory. The Event Counter can only be viewed using Pro-Link DDR.
                    </para>
                </item>
            </seqlist>
